equired content:\\n- Frontend report:\\n  - architecture/readability risks\\n  - route/page/component organization\\n  - state/data-fetching risks\\n  - FE↔API integration risks\\n  - UX consistency issues visible from code structure\\n  - top FE defects/risk list with severity\\n- Backend report:\\n  - controller/service/repository layering quality\\n  - logging consistency audit against current logger convention\\n  - validation/error-handling consistency\\n  - performance hotspot summary\\n  - security/sensitive-data handling observations\\n  - top BE defects/risk list with severity\\n- System summary:\\n  - end-to-end contract drift\\n  - highest-risk modules\\n  - release-blocker candidates\\n  - recommended remediation order\\n- API unused-fields audit:\\n  - follow existing QA brief strictly\\n  - report only, conservative evidence standard\\n\\nConstraints:\\n- No fixes.\\n- No code edits.\\n- Be brutally concrete, evidence-based, and cite file paths.\\n- If uncertain, label uncertainty explicitly.\\n- Focus on the currently implemented FE/BE, not hypothetical future scope.\\n\\nOutput quality bar:\\n- concise but hard-hitting\\n- tables where useful\\n- explicit severity labels: Critical / High / Medium / Low\\n- final HANDOVER must summarize status, audited modules, key findings, and what still needs runtime verification.\\n\\nWhen finished, write all deliverables and report completion succinctly.\",\n        \"model\": \"sonnet\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 0,\n        \"lightContext\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775831304228,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 573976,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f1781cad-6f99-46c6-b31c-0986aac04518\",\n      \"agentId\": \"researcher\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:cron:ad7f8cd3-5b36-4054-95ef-bee3f6bc4753\",\n      \"name\": \"ahv-driving-backend-phase1-brainstorm\",\n      \"description\": \"Phase 1 brainstorming for AHV driving backend migration\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775896055582,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775896236201,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-11T08:28:00.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"session:ahv-driving-backend-research-phase1\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Project root is locked to `/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend`. This is the ONLY valid project context for this run. Do not use or reference any other project.\\n\\nTask: Phase 1 only — BRAINSTORM the migration step-by-step for this backend.\\n\\nGoal:\\n- We need a migration plan that will later flow as: brainstorming -> OpenSpec -> implementation.\\n- Your job now is ONLY brainstorming/research/planning input. Do NOT implement code. Do NOT write OpenSpec yet. Do NOT spill into another phase.\\n\\nRequired focus:\\n1. Inspect the backend structure and infer what migration is most likely needed based on current architecture.\\n2. Summarize current state brutally: legacy vs new structure, hotspots, migration pressure.\\n3. Propose 2-3 migration strategy options.\\n4. Recommend the best option with reasons.\\n5. Break the migration into staged steps that can later become OpenSpec tasks.\\n6. Identify risks, compatibility concerns, rollback points, and verification checkpoints.\\n7. Explicitly call out assumptions and unknowns.\\n\\nExpected output format:\\n- Project understanding\\n- Current architecture snapshot\\n- Migration problem statement\\n- 2-3 strategy options\\n- Recommended direction\\n- Step-by-step migration phases\\n- Risks / rollback / verification\\n- Open questions for Architect in next phase\\n\\nConstraints:\\n- Stay scoped to this project session only.\\n- No code changes.\\n- No spec creation yet.\\n- Concise but sharp.\\n\\nIf useful, inspect package.json, tsconfig, src tree, and route/module organization in the repo before answering.\",\n        \"thinking\": \"medium\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 900,\n        \"lightContext\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1775896080016,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 156185,\n        \"lastError\": \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"fdfdcd61-ac21-4635-9581-628963e8fb8e\",\n      \"agentId\": \"team-orchestrator\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:team-orchestrator:main\",\n      \"name\": \"ahv-driving-route-map-now\",\n      \"enabled\": false,\n      \"deleteAfterRun\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1775865358779,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1775865559740,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"at\",\n        \"at\": \"2026-04-10T23:56:30.000Z\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Project root: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend\\n\\nYou are Researcher. Do not implement code. Read the real backend repo and produce a route/module mapping report.\\n\\nScope:\\n- Identify the HTTP entry flow from src/server.ts -> src/app.ts -> route registration.\\n- Enumerate mounted route groups under /api/v1.\\n- Map each module to its main controller/service/route files.\\n- Group modules by business domain.\\n